profile:
Thank you for visiting Envirotech Insulation and Envirotech Electrical Services Inc.   
 
We are a dual service organization, offering a full range of electrical services for commercial and residential, along with specializing in retrofit wall insulation, attic insulation, and garage ceiling insulation applications. We also offer removal of insulation. 
 
Over 28 years licensed in the electrical trade, with experience in residential, commercial, industrial, microfit and net metering solar installations, backup generators, Generlink transfer switches, aluminum wiring.  A member of the ACP program for electrical contractors, we can take care of all your electrical needs.
 
**We were the preferred electrical contractor for HGTV's DECKED OUT during their last season.**
 
Envirotech Insulation specializes in installing cellulose in walls, cavities, knee walls, garage ceilings, attics, and other area that might be inaccessible without having to remove plaster, or drywall.  Through infrared we can identify problem areas of air leakage, and missing or lack of insulation to help suggest the proper recommendations for increasing the energy efficiency and comfort in your home. We also offer dense packed cellulose insulation for soundproofing/noise reduction applications. We ensure intake venting is appropriate from the soffits, and exhaust fan are connected properly.  
www.envirotechinsulation.ca
 
Please contact us for an estimate, and to learn more about the products and services we offer

profile:
We are qualified full-service HVAC and Electrical Contractor, providing optimum Heating, Air Conditioning, Indoor Air Quality and Electrical Services to residents of Toronto since 1997. 
Our electricians are Master Electricians and our HVAC technicians are natural gas, propane and oil certified.
When you work with us, you have confidence that all installation, replacements and repairs carried out to comply with manufacturer instructions, and all the regulations with regard to Electrical(ESA), and Gas & Refrigeration(TSSA) are taken into account.

For more than 20 years, we build our business trust and reputation, by providing the best products and services to our clients. We design fully customized Heating, Cooling and Electrical solutions for every customer, providing the best match for your needs and budget.
If you are interested to get your new heating or cooling system with easy and low monthly payment plans, we are partner with Financeit, which is a leading company in financing.

Call (416)-822-9030
Whether you live in a heritage home or a newly built home, you can trust House Depot Home Services for the best results for your ultimate satisfaction.

profile:
We are committed to providing an excellent service across Toronto, GTA and nearby regions. In our decade of experience, we have learned that you can get your appliance, HVAC, electrical and plumbing issues repaired quickly, effectively, and relatively inexpensively. Our specialty is to provide quick solutions to all your appliance, plumbing, HVAC and electrical repairs and to achieve the highest possible customer satisfaction from our services. Our punctual and friendly staff will always provide budget-friendly repairs.

WHY DO OUR CUSTOMERS LOVE US?
"Slow is smooth, smooth is fast." This is our motto because we take exceptional care in locating your appliance and plumbing faults to have them fixed within the shortest possible period. We encourage our customers to watch us as we perform the repair and to ask as many questions as possible while we are on site. This will ensure the best service on the market because you will be educated on all of your appliances at no extra cost.
Man With a Wrench always provides an above and beyond service because we do not simply tackle the problem at hand. We also find its underlying cause. Most importantly, we provide our customers with education as to how to prevent such problems from occurring in the future. Our budget-friendly repairs are second to none and we will provide you with quick solutions to all of your appliance repair needs. Our goal is to delight you with our service. If you don’t go shouting from the rooftops how happy you are with your service following a work order, we will be very disappointed, for our business runs on word-of-mouth referrals and we strive to ensure you’re happy enough to tell your friends about our service

WHAT APPLIANCE REPAIR SERVICES DO WE OFFER?
We will repair any major appliance and any major brand for: 
- Refrigerators repair 
- Stove repair 
- Oven repair 
- Washing Machine repair 
- Dryer repair 
- Dishwasher repair 
- Microwave repair

We repair all makes and models, we even repair Miele appliances! Other brands we service regularly: Frigidaire, Simmons, Samsung, LG, GE, Kenmore, Thermadore, Whirlpool, Kenmore, Maytag, Moffat, Dacor, Fisher and Paykel, Thermador, Electrolux, Bosch, Sub Zero, Amana, Jenn-Air, Wolf, AEG, Magic Chef, Viking, Blomberg, Admiral, Westing House, Ariston, MagicChef, Inglis - IF THE Brand is not on the list WE CAN DO IT (we just missed it).

WHAT PLUMBING SERVICES DO WE OFFER?
- Toilet repair 
- Drain cleaning
- Plumbing repairs
- New installations (sinks, toilets, showers) 
- Water pumps
- Water heaters
- Frozen pipes
- Re-piping
- Burst Pipes
- Leak Detection 
- Inspections

We service Toronto and all surrounding areas. That includes: Toronto, Whitby, Oshawa, Pickering, Scarborough, Markham, Aurora, Newmarket, Brampton, Bradford, Oakville, Mississauga, Etobicoke, North York, East York, GTA, Burlington, Barrie, Innisfil and all of the cities that surround the cities listed


We look forward to servicing your appliance and plumbing HVAC and electrical repair needs!

profile:
Heating & Air Conditioning

COOLING
At Belyea Bros. we install and service a range of air conditioning systems including forced air (central) air conditioning, ductless split air conditioners, and our custom designed Attic Pak and SpacePak systems. Due to our background as a hot water heating specialists we are experts at planning and executing cooling solutions for houses without ductwork.

HEATING
At Belyea Bros. Limited we hold the first heating license issued in Toronto. As a result, we have the experience to claim, “there is nothing about heating we don’t know”. We are experts in hot water, radiant in-floor, snow melt systems and forced air heating. Over a number of years we have carefully selected the products that we recommend to our customers. We sell only manufacturers that have a proven track record of quality and service so that we can offer you the best support possible. All the manufacturers we work with have parts centers or distributors within the GTA meaning we have access to a local support network. We offer only reliable premium equipment.

HOT WATER TANKS 
Water heater rentals are a great solution for many homeowners who have a short-to-medium time frame in their house, own a tenanted property, are looking for a peace-of-mind solution to address their domestic hot water needs, or simply wish to have a clear idea of their monthly house budget over the long term without the worry of heater repairs.

Many consumers are confused by which company they actually rent their water heater from, thinking that because the charge appears on their gas bill that they rent from “gas-company”. In fact, most customers in Toronto rent their heaters from Centrica PLC, an international energy services company based in the United Kingdom, which operates in Canada under the brand name Direct Energy™. Although they bill on the gas bill, they are not, in any way, affiliated with your gas utility.

Belyea Bros. has a wide range of hot water tank solutions for your family’s needs. We have an excellent rental program providing a comparable rate and great reliable products. We provide a fix rate increase, unlike the other guys who may raise your billing at anytime. 

TANKLESS HOT WATER
Tankless hot water heaters are common in Europe and Japan. They can supply an endless supply of hot water, with greater energy savings than conventional tanks. They are, however, limited in the amount of hot water that can be produced at one time and the upfront costs are higher.

ELECTRICAL SERVICE
Belyea Bros. Electrical specializes in helping home and business owners in the older neighborhoods of Toronto. We provide electrical service, repair and installation whether it’s diagnosing and fixing a broken outlet, or re-wiring your whole home, Belyea Bros. Electrical is here to help.

profile:
Expert GTA Electric Inc  provides high-quality, price effective solutions for your home or business and our area of work is new construction, repair, maintenance and service.

We work on projects ranging from small residential installations to large scale commercial and industrial projects.
Expert GTA Electric Inc is the most trusted and effective Electrical Contractor to provide the most reliable, timely and cost-effective electrical services to our Residential, Commercial and Industrial clients.

We provide electrical services in the GTA area. Please Feel free to contact us for any Commercial, Industrial or Residential Electrical Services in the GTA area.
Contact us at 647 409 1488 for a free Electrical Service quote for any residential, commercial or industrial projects. 24-hour emergency services are available .


MAIN RESIDENTIAL SERVICES
Electrical Panel Upgrade
An electrical panel upgrade may be required due to renovation or because your current panel can no longer securely handle your home’s demands. You should know that only a licensed electrician can perform a panel upgrade. Your electrical panel is a vital component of your home and should be well maintained and highly functional. As your electrical needs evolve, you may need to modify your electrical panel to avoid safety difficulties and fire hazards. Additionally, all maintenance on your electrical panel should be performed by a certified electrician.

Electrical Wiring & Rewiring
There are a plethora of reasons why you might require wire installations in a new area of your house. If you need to wire light fixtures, track lighting, ceiling fans, new outlets, switches, electrical panels, sound systems, security cameras, or anything else our electrical team can help. Our electricians have worked on both Commercial and Residential wiring projects; this guarantees that we will be able to perform any electrical repair or installation required to make your property safe.

MAIN COMMERCIAL SERVICES
Electrical Repair & Trouble Shooting
Electrical issues can occur at any time. Our skilled and experienced professionals are available to respond swiftly to your electrical needs 7 days a week. Our electricians want to help you create the property of your dreams.

Lighting Systems
Having up-to-date lighting systems is energy efficient and beneficial for the environment. It allows you to fully harness the power your pre-existing electrical system offers with much higher reliability and lower maintenance.

MAIN INDUSTRIAL SERVICES
Industrial Process Improvement
Expert GTA Electric is a Toronto-based industrial electrical company committed to meeting all of your industrial electrical requirements while also delivering expert execution of electrical design-build solutions for your company.

In addition to installations and designs, our electricians also work on electrical repairs and upgrades as well as maintenance and troubleshooting. If you want to enhance energy efficiency while also increasing productivity and reducing downtime, we are the solution for you.

Industrial services include anything from lighting retrofits and solutions to Programmable Logic Control & Control Panel Design, as well as the installation of signs and panels, or power and distribution equipment installation.

Installation of lights and smoke detectors
Expert GTA Electric is the electrical business to call when you need the installation of fire protective/preventive devices. All workplaces are required to have a smoke detection system by law. Hardwired smoke detectors are the most effective method of protecting those we care about. Expert GTA Electric can install and change the smoke detector system in your company, ensuring that you are protected at all times. Our experts will carry out a thorough investigation to personalize our services to your specific needs.

Expert GTA Electric can also assist you to save money on energy costs. We recommend that our clients switch to LED retrofit lighting. This can save electricity use by up to 70 percent while also lasting 25 times longer than incandescent bulbs. This installation should be completed by a certified electrician.

We have over 20 years experience in home electrical repairs, upgrades, and complete system installations. We are knowledgeable about all sorts of jobs, large and small, and our professional speedy service has been verified by our past happy clients. Safety and due diligence are our top priority, and we have the certifications to prove our commitment to these important aspects of residential electrical services.	

Each job must be done with care, and our adherence to federal and provincial standards means that you get quality installations that stand the test of time. Whenever and wherever you need home electrical installations, upgrades, or repairs, we would be happy to help. Our experienced and knowledgeable services will get the job done efficiently and effectively. Trust us with your residential electrical needs when you are in need of an expert.

REPAIRS AND SMALL HOME ELECTRICAL JOBS
NO MATTER THE JOB SIZE, WE CAN HELP WITH YOUR HOME ELECTRICAL
If you need a home electrical repair or small job completed we would be happy to hear from you. We are experienced and quick when it comes to responding, assessing, and conducting residential repairs. We offer high quality work so that your electrical problem will be solved efficiently and your new components will stand the test of time. We can also advise you on the best way to resolve your electrical needs, including choosing the most affordable yet reliable components for your small electrical repair or project.	
Our home repair services include troubleshooting electrical outlets, light fixtures, light switches, telephone connections, internet connections, television connections, and more. We can help whether you are installing a new outlet, fixture, or other small electrical component, and we are capable of replacement jobs if you need something repaired or upgraded. If there is something small that needs to be upgraded to code we are competent with handling that. We also do outdoor home electrical installations and repairs if the issue is located outside your home.

HOME SYSTEM INSTALLATIONS AND UPGRADES
MANAGING AND COMPLETING YOUR LARGER HOME ELECTRICAL PROJECTS

Whether you are building a new residence or need to upgrade your home's entire electrical system, look no further than Geebo Electrical. We can handle your entire project from start to finish, including working from build diagrams, advising on the best installation methods, sourcing and budgeting for electrical components, and project managing. Once installed we inspect and test the integrity of your entire system to ensure every single component is working correctly. Beyond the system installation we do install light fixtures, switches, outlets, and other components needed to ensure that every detail of your electrical system is covered and ready-to-use when our work is completed.
	
We are capable of home electrical system upgrades, including removing old electrical hardware and installing new hardware. Ensuring your residence is up to code is important not only for your family's safety and security, but for legal purposes which can increase the resale value of your property. Contact us today to discuss the details of your project. We would be happy to advise you on the best route and most affordable, safe, quality components you will need. It's important to us that you feel confident and calm about your new electrical system and the installation process.

profile:
For over 36 years, we've built a reputation in the Durham Region and Greater Toronto Area electrical industry as being honest and committed to customer satisfaction. Today we continue to practice these same values that have helped our company grow over the years.
 
Our technicians are industry leading. They work carefully and efficiently, and treat your home or place of business with respect, while ensuring the job gets done right. Our technicians are clean, uniformed, courteous, and even wear shoe covers to help preserve your floors. At Rand Electric we value your time. This means that we will schedule your service within a small time window, and will call when we are on our way. This way you don't have to wait around all day wondering when someone will show up, leaving you to carry on with your busy life.
 
When you contact Rand Electric for any of your electrical needs, we'll send a technician to your home or business who will diagnose your situation, explain your options in simple, easy-to-understand terms, and wait for your approval before beginning the work. This way you have the knowledge to make an informed decision.
 
Our service vans carry thousands of parts! Because of our fully stocked service vehicles, over 90% of our services can be delivered on the spot, saving you time and money.

Canadian Electrical Upgrades would be happy to become a small or a big part of your next project. We can help with projects as small as changing light fixtures, to full Knob and Tube removal.
